<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-17T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-17T23:00:00-05:00" n="170" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d170">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">868.01/416: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador to the Greek Government in Exile</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">at Cairo</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-18T00:00:00-04:00">December
                                    18, 1943—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Greek [Series] 63. A complete reversal of British policy toward the Greek
                            King seems indicated in your Greek 128, December 12, 10 a.m. and 130,
                            December 14, 10 a.m.<note n="62" xml:id="d170fn62">Latter not
                                printed.</note> Please report any obtainable information as to
                            reasons for this change.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>